verbs.description: rehaul (third-person singular simple present rehauls, present participle rehauling, simple past and past participle rehauled)

examples: Certainly there is nothing in the letter to obligate the Government to pay for the rehauling of the 3,421 tons of coal from the storage point to the claimant's powerhouse.
Almost immediately, however, trouble with the throttle forced the ship to make a short stop in Copenhagen, site of its manufacture, to have its engine rehauled.
